Midgaard's Guard Command officer corps is substantially composed of academy-trained Knights. Guard doctrine of wall defense, convoy escort, and emergency response maps well onto Knight formation principles. The primary political tension concerns the Compact of the Seven Chains: doctrine governs over employer loyalty. Modern Guard Command Knights are usually aligned — civic authority and Knight doctrine rarely conflict — but the tradition holds that when they do, doctrine governs. Continuity faction is comfortable with this in theory and uncomfortable when specific Guard Command officers cite doctrine reasons for refusing specific directives. Knight academy credentials are recognized by guild courts the Lantern Reforms established, giving practitioners formal standing in commercial dispute resolution as well as military function.

