Kowloon's Wardens of Iron share provisioning doctrine and emergency charter frameworks with Midgaard's Guard Command under a formal bilateral agreement including mutual credential recognition. Knights operating under Warden of Iron auspices encounter a more explicitly labor-relations-oriented culture. Tactical command chains are complicated by Kowloon's district-color governance structure: five civic institutions hold overlapping jurisdictions that don't always map onto tactical command hierarchies. The Compact's principle — doctrine over employer — manifests differently when "employer" is ambiguous across five overlapping authorities. Warden of Iron officers who are Knight-trained have developed informal protocols for resolving overlapping authority questions that exist parallel to the formal governance structure.

