Mafdet's Harbor Wardens maintain a maritime escort function drawing on Knight training through a separate institutional framework from the inland equivalent. Maritime convoy escort has formation discipline requirements analogous to road escort but adapted to shipboard and dock conditions: smaller formation sizes, different terrain constraints, and boarding-and-repelling scenarios road escort does not encounter. Mafdet recognizes Knight academy credentials but requires supplementary maritime escort certification for Harbor Warden service. The Strandline Compact's trade network generates consistent demand for Knight-trained escort personnel, making Mafdet one of the larger tradition employers in the five-city network despite its smaller civic size.

