Ashborn forge-culture approaches Knight formation doctrine with a practical orientation: formations are structures that succeed through correct construction and fail through structural weakness. The Compact's three-principle motto maps onto forge-work structure — the breaking force is the striking blow, the holding discipline is the temper keeping the blade from shattering, the recovery commitment is the reforging when the work is damaged. Ashborn Knights in Midgaard's Guard Command tend toward the defensive discipline end of the formation spectrum. Guard Command officers note Ashborn Knights are exceptionally reliable in sustained siege defense and require more encouragement than average in rapid aggressive advance scenarios.

