Khephari cyclical endurance doctrine produces Knights who understand the formation's primary function as structural durability across extended engagements rather than peak aggressive performance at initial contact. The Compact's principle that formation discipline produces force multiplication over time aligns with Khephari understanding that what endures through repeated stress is what matters. Khephari Knights in Kiess's Roc Road escort function are valued for extended operations unfolding over days rather than hours — contexts where psychological formation is more determinative than raw combat technique. Wall Command after-action assessments consistently note Khephari Knight effectiveness in extended frontier engagement contexts where other practitioners' discipline degraded.

